Title: Exact Scale Invariance of the BF-Yang-Mills Theory in Three Dimensions
Authors: Oswaldo M. Del Cima, Daniel H. T. Franco, Jose A. Helayel-Neto and
  Olivier Piguet
Comments: 11 pages, Latex
Report-no: CBPF-NF-017/98 and UFES-DF-OP98/2
Journal-ref: JHEP 9804 (1998) 010
\\
  The ``extended'' BF-Yang-Mills theory in 3 dimensions, which contains a
minimally coupled scalar field, is shown to be ultraviolet finite. It obeys a
trivial Callan-Symanzik equation, with all beta-functions and anomalous
dimensions vanishing. The proof is based on an anomaly-free trace identity
valid to all orders of perturbation theory.
